# Coplay Unity MCP — Universal Template

Live Editor integration via `com.coplaydev.unity-mcp` (v10+). Cursor server name: `user-unityMCP`.

## Transport (this project)

- **Use stdio** — configured in user `~/.cursor/mcp.json` with `uvx` and `mcpforunityserver==<plugin version>`.
- **Windows:** bootstrap writes hidden launcher to `~/.cursor/scripts/unity-mcp-hidden.ps1` and patches `mcp.json` (no blank console window).
- **Version sync:** first project open applies stdio prefs; `CoplayMcpSetupMenu` rewrites `mcp.json` when the Unity package version changes (Coplay auto-migration is blocked by `LockCursorConfig` — intentional).
- **Do not** open MCP For Unity → Start Server on Unity **6.5** (UI crash). Stdio bridge auto-starts on Editor idle.
- HTTP (`localhost:8080`) is a fallback only when stdio is unavailable; document crash risk.

## Session startup

When Unity Editor is open and MCP is connected:

1. Resource `mcpforunity://instances` — one instance, or `set_active_instance` if several.
2. Resource `mcpforunity://editor/state` — wait for `isCompiling: false` and `ready_for_tools: true`.
3. Activate tool groups for the task:

| Group | Tools | When |
|-------|-------|------|
| **core** (default on) | scenes, GameObjects, components, assets, prefabs, materials, cameras, physics, graphics/URP, build, packages, editor control, scripts, search | always when Editor connected |
| **asset_gen** | `generate_model`, `generate_image`, `import_model`, `import_model_file` | AI 3D/2D asset gen (BYO API keys) |
| **animation** | `manage_animation` | Animator, clips, controllers |
| **docs** | `unity_reflect`, `unity_docs` | API verification before new C# |
| **testing** | `run_tests`, `get_test_job` | UTR runs |
| **ui** | `manage_ui` | UXML/USS / UIDocument |
| **scripting_ext** | `manage_scriptable_object`, `execute_code` | SO assets; `execute_code` = diagnostics only |
| **profiling** | `manage_profiler` | perf / memory / frame debugger |
| **probuilder** | `manage_probuilder` | greybox / mesh editing (experimental) |
| **vfx** | `manage_vfx`, `manage_shader`, `manage_texture` | VFX Graph — **`vfx_*` only** (see `unity-vfx.mdc`) |

`manage_tools(action="activate", group="<name>")` — then `list_groups` to confirm.

### Core tool inventory (`group: core`)

| Tool | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `manage_scene` | load/save/hierarchy/validate scenes |
| `manage_gameobject` | create/move/rename/delete GameObjects |
| `manage_components` | add/remove/set component properties |
| `find_gameobjects` | search scene by name/tag/layer/component/path |
| `manage_prefabs` | create/modify prefab contents, prefab stage |
| `manage_asset` | CRUD, search, folders, duplicate, move, rename |
| `manage_material` | materials and shader property assignment |
| `manage_camera` | Cinemachine cameras, lens, targets, screenshots |
| `manage_physics` | layers matrix, materials, joints, raycasts, rigidbodies |
| `manage_graphics` | URP volumes, fog/skybox/ambient, light bake, pipeline |
| `manage_build` | build settings, scenes in build, trigger builds |
| `manage_packages` | install/remove/search packages, registries |
| `manage_editor` | play/pause/stop, tags/layers, undo/redo |
| `create_script`, `manage_script`, `apply_text_edits`, `script_apply_edits`, `delete_script`, `validate_script`, `get_sha` | C# scripts |
| `read_console` | errors/warnings after changes |
| `refresh_unity` | force asset refresh when external edits were unavoidable |
| `execute_menu_item` | Editor menu actions (read `mcpforunity://menu-items` first) |
| `find_in_file` | search inside project files via Unity |
| `batch_execute` | batch multiple MCP commands |

Other groups: `generate_*` / `import_*` (**asset_gen**), `manage_animation` (**animation**), `manage_ui` (**ui**), `manage_scriptable_object` / `execute_code` (**scripting_ext**), `manage_profiler` (**profiling**), `manage_probuilder` (**probuilder**), `manage_vfx` / `manage_shader` / `manage_texture` (**vfx**), `unity_reflect` / `unity_docs` (**docs**), `run_tests` / `get_test_job` (**testing**).

## MCP-first policy

When Unity Editor is open, MCP is connected, and `editor_state.ready_for_tools` is true — **use MCP first** for any row below. Fall back to workspace file tools only when MCP is offline, compile/domain reload is pending, or no tool covers the task.

| Task | Prefer MCP | Fallback (file tools) |
|------|------------|----------------------|
| Scenes / hierarchy | `manage_scene`, `find_gameobjects` | never hand-edit `.unity` YAML |
| GameObjects / components | `manage_gameobject`, `manage_components` | — |
| Prefabs | `manage_prefabs` (+ `manage_gameobject` in prefab stage) | — |
| Assets (any type) | `manage_asset` (search/create/modify/move/rename) | — |
| Materials | `manage_material` (**core**) | — |
| Shaders / textures | `manage_shader`, `manage_texture` (activate **vfx**) | — |
| AI 3D/2D assets | `generate_model`, `generate_image`, `import_model`, `import_model_file` (activate **asset_gen**) | — |
| ScriptableObjects | `manage_scriptable_object` (activate **scripting_ext**) | `.asset` YAML only if MCP fails |
| UI Toolkit | `manage_ui` + `get_visual_tree` / `render_ui` | UXML/USS file edit if Editor offline |
| Scripts | `create_script`, `apply_text_edits`, `script_apply_edits`, `manage_script`, `get_sha` | large multi-file refactors |
| Cameras / Cinemachine | `manage_camera` | — |
| Animation | `manage_animation` (activate **animation**) | — |
| VFX Graph | `manage_vfx` (`vfx_*` only) | — |
| ProBuilder greybox | `manage_probuilder` | — |
| Physics / colliders | `manage_physics` | — |
| Rendering / URP / fog / volumes | `manage_graphics` | — |
| Packages | `manage_packages` | `Packages/manifest.json` if MCP unavailable |
| Build settings / player build | `manage_build` | — |
| Play mode / tags / layers | `manage_editor` | — |
| Tests | `run_tests`, `get_test_job` (activate **testing**) | — |
| Perf / memory | `manage_profiler` (activate **profiling**) | — |
| Console / compile errors | `read_console` | — |
| API names / signatures | `unity_reflect`, `unity_docs` | `@Docs` |
| Editor diagnostics | `execute_code` (read-only probes) | not for shipping gameplay code |

**Do not:** write `.meta` by hand, patch scene/prefab YAML, or guess layout when MCP can attach assets and return resolved styles.

**Always after MCP mutations:** `read_console` or wait for `isCompiling: false` before depending on new types/components.

### File tools only (no MCP equivalent)

- `.asmdef`, `.inputactions`, `.cursor/rules`, docs, git — no dedicated MCP tool
- Sweeping refactors across many C# files at once
- Third-party vendored code under `Assets/Plugins/` unless explicitly editing via MCP scripts
- When Unity Editor is **closed** or MCP bridge is **down**

## Optional MCP deps (pre-installed in template)

Hub template ships MCP optional dependencies so new projects start with full agent tooling:

| Dependency | Location / package | Unlocks |
|------------|-------------------|---------|
| Roslyn | `Assets/Plugins/Roslyn/` | `execute_code` with C# 12+ (Roslyn) |
| ProBuilder | via `feature.worldbuilding` → `com.unity.probuilder` | `manage_probuilder` |
| Cinemachine | `com.unity.cinemachine` | enhanced `manage_camera` |
| VFX Graph | `com.unity.visualeffectgraph` | `manage_vfx` (VFX Graph paths) |
| glTFast | `com.unity.cloud.gltfast` | GLB/GLTF import for **asset_gen** (`import_model`, `import_model_file`) |

Versions are pinned in `Packages/manifest.json`. Do not remove vendored UniRx/Roslyn without updating MCP workflow.

